elements.2211.03173_1933aaf15ce4e83d258d8e7a5e70c: This paper presents a proof-of-concept method for classifying chemical compounds directly from NMR data without doing structure elucidation
elements.2211.03173_71a9e0ec409e0d0ddea7a8b142e36: This can help to reduce time in finding good structure candidates, as in most cases matching must be done by a human engineer, or at the very least a process for matching must be meaningfully interpreted by one
elements.2211.03173_8d9b9f9b7f27bb91019d9b7317c6b: Therefore, for a long time automation in the area of NMR has been actively sought
elements.2211.03173_a1cafc3c6824efe853d096df6bbf0: The method identified as suitable for the classification is a convolutional neural network (CNN)
elements.2211.03173_107541c9ce967b973fdd44d2f73f0: Other methods, including clustering and image registration, have not been found suitable for the task in a comparative analysis
elements.2211.03173_d32cce3f8568127c3e265816cd13c: The result shows that deep learning can offer solutions to automation problems in cheminformatics.
elements.2211.03173_d4df6ba34933ae2cf3e274a84d5ef: Nuclear Magnetic Resonance (NMR) spectroscopy is an established technique in analytical chemistry
elements.2211.03173_663aee71a43b919e81f6ad4e10401: As a result of its rich structural and dynamic information content, it is particularly suitable for compound identification
elements.2211.03173_e104e580ce31c8cc759736bc1e61a: However, a full elucidation may not always be possible or even necessary since some properties might be achievable directly from the spectra
elements.2211.03173_4c21aaa899ecaebf71bf45d088f5c: If this is the case, a prioritisation of substances to be closely investigated for compound assignment can be done in the early stages of a study
elements.2211.03173_8b8200852cf251a47eff973e3509e: A previous example for this idea was demonstrated in
elements.2211.03173_f500cb8e9125b006c063ee10d9cc3: , where the authors showed that the existence of certain substructures can be concluded from profiles in the spectra
elements.2211.03173_744be1be63c35ca843c59399ad72b: Another potentially useful application is chemical classification
elements.2211.03173_c253e687b73d544ed6c33f4a23d8c: These rely strongly on annotated chemical entities to provide a computable chemical taxonomy based on substructures
elements.2211.03173_25d0150a4f5b0cd54e3208eec0edd: In this paper, we infer that chemical taxonomy from the spectra
elements.2211.03173_ca6cbb9c5140190f9b4fbe189b2e9: Similar approach have been applied with Mass Spectrometry (MS) data where chemical classifications can be achieved from fragmentation patterns on MS/MS data
elements.2211.03173_fd37f5f2ca2474e436eb85ad477dc: , chemical classification is proven to be a valuable tool for compound annotation of unknown compounds and for classification of samples for prioritization for example
elements.2211.03173_421d34c78c16db6b709e2832391bf: The authors have decided to work with spectral images in this current study, but working with raw data would be another option
elements.2211.03173_f7eee72caf27fa188cd13728acdc7: By working with the images, this frames the problem very much as a digital image processing and machine vision methodology
elements.2211.03173_048ea28966f03507ff451a14d48a0: Computer science has developed a vast range of techniques here, in particular over the last few years, with image processing gaining importance in areas like autonomous driving or security monitoring (see
elements.2211.03173_b05b89de145215735b63e96459745: Whilst these techniques are mostly used to process video or photographic images, they can also be used to process data from scientific instruments
elements.2211.03173_45f4f0d75b951b8e51e3f6fa47a1c: Considering this, in this paper we want to examine the question if chemical class can be deducted directly from NMR spectra, using digital image processing techniques
elements.2211.03173_304c67cc56a4fac3185d6a09761ac: If so, the best method will be identified.

elements.2211.03173_9394e334ad3fda9a5b9df7b33f995: Image registration in general means transforming different sets of data into one coordinate system
elements.2211.03173_659bb796de34239e21e6ebbecfc5a: A typical application would be to align MRI images of different slices of a human brain
elements.2211.03173_a0d7ece024b29c97eb148c31823b1: For our purposes, we are measuring the amount of transformation needed to align two spectra
elements.2211.03173_2300faafa7f6cdc3c9261f62ae549: Similar to the image similarity calculation, our hypotheses is that spectra for compounds from the same class would require less change to align
elements.2211.03173_af61697a959fe6b1774c14d18d871: In order to test this we have used the image registration program VoxelMorph
elements.2211.03173_9745fa667e722f1d34593e0047320: VoxelMorph is based on deep learning and is considered an advanced image registration technique
elements.2211.03173_7380d6a913c91154cbbd39e85551d: We train it with the images of one class and then try to register images from the same and other classes to see the changes necessary
elements.2211.03173_4ae3b46c09d2196e263b65ae6e84e: folder in the GitHub repository of the project.

elements.2211.03173_b29221ca1691fd6a75e0a3dab986b: Convolutional neural networks (CNNs) have become a popular choice for many tasks, in particular image processing
elements.2211.03173_ca1f4bd28308f8a51c17969208392: Typical tasks here are image classification (e. g. find all images in a set which contain a car) or image segmentation (find all cars in an image)
elements.2211.03173_ee7f6f3b99f91fee8b3c3685775a7: The authors are not covering details of the working and the many applications here, for details and literature references see e. g. the recent review
elements.2211.03173_af94110f87682065b3aa186d76995: What is important in this context is the ability of CNNs to extract complex information
elements.2211.03173_9993ee912fc0eee15cff5d710d22c: that chemical information is accessible for CNNs from image representation of NMR spectra
elements.2211.03173_8b001559f5870f23dab75fe1f2ee4: It has also been shown that CNNs can process raw data of NMR spectra
elements.2211.03173_f69f4e4ee737b075502d42d8d9f64: This paper focuses purely on the visual information
elements.2211.03173_b51d5bf34fc288600c7afb399141a: The authors used the same networks as in

elements.2211.03173_0faee90659774545b4a694f1becdc: This network has been trained with HMBC and HSQC separately

elements.2211.03173_e77c2b460332d118dfb8acbb0ad96: This combined CNN architecture consists of 2 initial branches, forming independent CNNs, which are then connected to a dense layer and followed by an output layer
elements.2211.03173_fecc3de4cbfe2111a4084aaca02b3: The networks are implemented with Python 3 using Keras and Tensorflow libraries
elements.2211.03173_1aad403910d5437ca17fed02d6c23: Furthermore, this study assumes a closed-world hypothesis, where all compounds fall in exactly one category (i.e. are of exactly one superclass)

elements.2211.03173_f543ecd2c85b9d3e6b093fc767857: We have shown that CNNs are able to extract chemical class information from NMR spectra
elements.2211.03173_1be2dd6657d9805398a3a6c51a5d3: This is in contrast to other image processing methods, which are not able to do so
